This repository contains the Python implementation of the Error‑Projected Recurrent Neural Network (EP‑RNN) framework for time series forecasting. The code implements modified recurrent architectures in which an error‑projection signal is injected into the gating mechanisms of recurrent cells (e.g., LSTM, GRU, and BiLSTM).

The core idea is to compute a corrective signal based on the difference between the current input‑aligned proposal and the propagated hidden state, and then project this signal into the hidden space of the network. This projected error is used to modulate the internal gates of the recurrent units during training, enabling the model to better adapt to noisy, missing, or outlier‑contaminated time series data.

Reference

If you use this code in your research, please cite the following paper:

Jahani, A., Khalilpour, S. A., Seyedi, H., Taghirad, H. D., & Najafi, E. (2026). EP‑RNN: Error‑projected recurrent neural network for time series forecasting. Results in Engineering, 30, 110454. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.rineng.2026.110454
